text: Kebraty () is a rural locality (a settlement) and the administrative center of Kebratskoye Rural Settlement, Gaynsky District, Perm Krai, Russia. The population was 858 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km north-west from Gayny. == References == Category:Rural localities in Gaynsky District
title: Kebraty
